  "prompt": "What can substitute butter in a brownies recipe?",
  "response": "There are several substitutes for butter in a brownie recipe, depending on your dietary preferences and the texture you desire:\n\n1. **Vegetable Oil**: Canola oil, sunflower oil, or any neutral oil can be used. Use about 3/4 of the amount of butter called for in the recipe.\n\n2. **Coconut Oil**: This will add a slight coconut flavor. Use it in a 1:1 ratio to replace butter.\n\n3. **Applesauce**: For a lower-fat option, unsweetened applesauce can be used. Replace butter with applesauce in a 1:1 ratio, but note that this may make the brownies denser and moister.\n\n4. **Nut Butters**: Almond butter or peanut butter can add a rich flavor. Use it in a 1:1 ratio to replace butter, but be aware that it will change the flavor.\n\n5. **Greek Yogurt**: This is another healthier alternative. Use 1/2 the amount of butter and replace it with Greek yogurt to keep the brownies moist.\n\n6. **Silken Tofu**: Blended silken tofu can be used as a butter substitute. Use about 1/4 cup of blended tofu for each 1/2 cup of butter.\n\n7. **Margarine**: A straightforward substitute, use it in a 1:1 ratio to replace butter.\n\n8. **Vegan Buttery Spreads**: These can be used in the same amount as butter.\n\nWhen substituting, keep in mind that the texture and flavor of the brownies may vary slightly based on the substitute used.",
